to sit and watch something swing in and out of control. was there ever control? 
did you ever know the mind of me? have you looked twice at the picture? i doubt. if you did i know you would have done something. the hardest to accept is pain that almost is self inflicting...by not making a move. not moving my pon to get out of the way of you queen. you are the queen. i am the beginner. you are an intermidete. my level of skill in these games is too low to make a difference. a lucky move once in a while doesn't cut it. making the team was something of a hobby. nothing more. until you pushed me to be the best i could be. and i am still in your shadow. 

i am sick of the shadow, sick of the invisable lines i put up for myself, sick of your careless mistakes that keep you safe and in company.

have you ever even known alone?

Sometimes you will notice things that you don't expect about yourself. Such as the ablity to not be able to commit. Something that i have been able to aquire over the years of my life. For some reason the last week or two has had me reflect upon this and i seem to push people away when i feel as though i have the potentional of getting too close to them. because i know once i reach a certain point i am going to be too hurt and now i am mad at myself for doing this to myself because now i know that there could have been good potentional in the past and i didn't persue it and i don't even know now how too to persue it. God and i have now put up a nice little emo journal, but i guess that part of LJ, eh? I am too sick of thinking about both of those topics today so i think my best bet is to sleep because i can't start packing tonight.
